<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="Dumbbell-Cross-Body-Hammer-Curl">Dumbbell Cross-Body Hammer Curl</h3>



<p>The <a href="https://www.endomondo.com/exercise/dumbbell-cross-body-hammer-curl" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">dumbbell cross-body curl</a> uses the same elbow action as the dumbbell bicep curl. However, it differs in its movement pattern, allowing targeted muscle activation.</p>



<p>Because it uses a neutral hammer grip, it targets the brachialis and brachioradialis alongside both bicep heads. Whilst not technically classed as part of the bicep, these are key elbow flexors that help with overall bicep thickness and, therefore, appearance.</p>



