<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Anatomy Of The Biceps</h2>



<p>Your <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK519538/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">biceps brachii</a> are located at the front of your upper arms, going from your shoulder blades to your forearms. They’re made up of two main muscle heads that vary in location and function. These are your biceps short head and biceps long head.&nbsp;</p>


