<p class="has-large-font-size">Expert tip</p>



<p>For a bigger muscle-building stimulus, squeeze your biceps at the top of the movement.</p>
</div></div>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading list-start">Anatomy Of The Triceps</h2>



<p>Your <a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK536996/#:~:text=The%20primary%20function%20of%20the,form%20a%20single%20tendon%20distally." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">triceps brachii</a> are located at the back of your upper arm, directly opposite your biceps brachii. They make up almost two-thirds of your upper arm, making them an important part of your arm training.</p>



<p>They’re made up of three main muscle heads that also differ in location and function. These are your triceps lateral heads, triceps medial heads, and triceps long heads.</p>


